{
  "text": "The significance of the random effects was obtained through Deviance Analysis, using the REML method (Restricted Maximum Likelihood), via LRT (Likelihood Ratio Test). The deviances were obtained as described by [CITATION_1] , using the model with and without the respective effects, subtracting the deviance obtained in the complete model, of the model without the effect, and compared to the value of the Chi-square (\u03c7\u00b2) at 1% probability, with one degree of freedom. The factor block, considered as fixed effect, was tested by the F test of Snedecor.",
